{
  "stem": "19969.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They killed them all with their bare hands and I suspect with boards and whatever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It-- and then we find the evidence of gruesome medical experiments from Dr.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Schilling and one other doctor [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] performed experiments on-- Rasher, it was Dr.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Rasher performed gruesome medical experiments on the people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Usually, all the experiments ended up in a rather agonizing death.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they had pictures of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they were used in the war crimes trial.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Germans were great picture takers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember they had pictures of a-- one prisoner they had in some kind of pressure chamber and they would simulate different altitudes.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is for the Luftwaffe, the German Air Force, apparently, to see how-- at what altitude they would die.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they had them in these pressure chambers and it showed a man gradually dying as they reduced the pressure.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The human body literally explodes when they get to zero-- down to zero pressure.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then the other experiment he was conducting for the Luftwaffe was to see how people could-- how long they could exist in cold water.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they'd start out at degrees like 40 degrees and strip them naked and then get down to 30 degrees and see how long they lasted at various temperatures.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Presumably, this was for the German Air Force in case they ditched out over the sea.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So those were agonizing deaths, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There were those two doctors who performed I think practically all of the experiments there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There were all kinds of pictures of brutality at the-- like people hanging up to a tree by their hands.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
